  "text": "The mouse APLPs, like βPP, are transcriptionally active in brain [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . We find that Fe65 has a similar spatial pattern of expression in mouse brain, and is abundantly expressed in human brain. We have characterized a novel human Fe65 cDNA which is highly homologous to the rat sequence; however, the human sequence predicts a unique 78 amino acid N-terminal extension not present in the rat protein. The human Fe65 gene maps to human chromosome 11p15.",
